programme.title: Fiesta de la Tradición
programme.desc: In the Argentinian equivalent of a rodeo, horsemen, or gauchos, compete in the annual festival. Once a year, gauchos from all over the country gather in Argentina to show off their equestrian skills in a week-long festival dating back to 1939. The Gaucho Games are the main attraction at the Jineteada, the Argentine version of a rodeo.

programme.title: Colours of the rhythm
programme.desc: Helped by colourful lighting, two stylistically different dancers interpret the same music in their own way. Two stylistically different dancers interpret the same music in their own personal way. With the addition of colourful lighting, their moves create visual art that expresses the rhythm of the music.

programme.title: The Driven
programme.desc: At the pinnacle of performance, natural ability only goes so far. Drive separates the good from the great. The elite performers in any field share a common thread of unstoppable work ethic. Olympic gold medallist sprinter Michael Johnson and America's Cup-winning skipper Jimmy Spithill tell their stories of success through a drive to continually improve.

programme.title: Semenuk's Rad Company
programme.desc: Brandon Semenuk and an elite group of pros raise the bar on freeride mountain bike insanity. Brandon Semenuk captures some of the highest level freeride mountain biking ever attempted in this cinematic party. He picks his favourite riders to show off their insane skills on some of the best natural and man-made terrain on earth.

programme.title: Etnies: Chapters
programme.sub-title: Finding the world's best BMX spots
programme.desc: Enjoy groundbreaking riding captured in the most desirable BMX spots in the world. This team endured countless injuries and dedicated endless hours in search of the most desirable BMX spots in the world to bring you groundbreaking riding captured through the unique perspective of filmmakers Will Stroud and Mike Manzoori.

programme.title: Age of Ondra part 2
programme.desc: Adam Ondra challenges himself to flash a 9A+, which means he only gets one ascent to make it to the top. Adam Ondra has learned to focus on climbing better technically, as well as building strength. Ondra challenges himself to flash a 9A+, which means he only gets one ascent to make it to the top.

programme.title: The Unifiers
programme.desc: Artists like Wyclef Jean and Paul van Dyk may have grown up isolated, but now seek to bring people together. Despite growing up on different sides of the globe, Paul van Dyk and Wyclef Jean shared the experience of an early life filled with strife and isolation. But these great artists channelled that into an unquenchable desire to bring people together.

programme.title: The Blue Armada
programme.desc: An award-winning Russian motorsports team show their unique way of working and preparing for the Dakar Rally. The most famous and award-winning motorsports team in Russia use their unique way of working together to prepare for off-road racing's most prestigious event, the Dakar Rally.

programme.title: The Silent Samurai
programme.sub-title: A look back at Dani Pedrosa's career
programme.desc: Take a look at the key moments that made Dani Pedrosa one of the most talented riders of his generation. Enjoy a look back at Dani Pedrosa’s motorcycling career as seen through the eyes of his coach, friend and former MotoGP star Sete Gibernau. Relive the key moments that made him one of the most talented riders of his generation.

programme.title: Rich + Tone: PolyRhythmic
programme.desc: Choreography team Rich + Tone take it back to their roots as they talk about their career in the dance world. Brothers Richmond and Anthony Talauega have been behind some of pop music's most explosive dance performances. Their inspiration for dancing comes from their heritage and upbringing, which they revisit as they craft a major routine for Chris Brown.

programme.title: What Lies Ahead
programme.desc: The b-boys consider their futures. Roxrite judges a competition. Neguin visits friends. Lilou makes a choice. The b-boys get honest with themselves while setting their future goals. Roxrite judges a BC One qualifier. Neguin takes his nephew to an open b-boy practice session. After some soul-searching, Lilou opts to go for a third world championship.

programme.title: The Learning Curve
programme.sub-title: Drew Bezanson: From BMX to MTB
programme.desc: Drew Bezanson tries to make the transition from freestyle BMX to the world of slopestyle mountain biking. To be a master of two sports is a feat many have tried but few have accomplished. Drew Bezanson is one of the top BMX riders in the world, but now he wants to enter the world of slopestyle mountain biking and compete at Red Bull Joyride.

programme.title: Wingmen
programme.desc: Three elite BASE jumpers face the unknown on a global journey to find the best wingsuit and BASE jump spots. Three of the world's best wingsuit flyers set out on a global journey in search of perfect spots for proximity flying and BASE jumps. From Brazil to China, the trio face some of the most thrilling and challenging flights of their lives.

programme.title: Turn up in Tahiti
programme.desc: The whole crew take off from Maui and head to Teahupo'o, Tahiti, where they immediately hit the waves. The whole crew take off from Maui and head to Teahupo'o, Tahiti, where they immediately hit the waves despite the rain. Then it's time for another round of Poopies riding his way down a mountainside.

programme.title: Peter Conroy
programme.desc: Peter Conroy is a firefighter who runs into danger on a daily basis to feed his passion for chasing huge surf. Peter Conroy works in Dublin as a firefighter, and after bills are paid, he has about €50 for the month — which he puts towards surfing. Conroy's deep passion for chasing big waves at one of Ireland's scariest slabs is nothing short of inspiring.

programme.title: Barry Mottershead
programme.desc: A self-employed South African relocates to Ireland to pursue his dream of surfing giant waves in the Atlantic. Barry Mottershead, a South African who now lives in Ireland, works as a kayak tour guide to make ends meet. But his passion lies in surfing the massive slabs at Mullaghmore. He is a man who charts his own course and does what it takes to surf.

programme.title: Andrew Cotton
programme.desc: A family man works as a lifeguard full-time to be in the physical and financial shape to surf giant waves. Andrew Cotton is a lifeguard, a family man, and a Billabong XXL Award contender. He saves lives for a career as a lifeguard, builds homes with his bare hands as a necessity, and surfs the biggest waves he can find for fun.

programme.title: Hugo Vau
programme.desc: Being in the sea keeps this fisherman connected to his passion for surfing and lets him live the way he wants. Hugo Vau's life revolves around the ocean. He is a fisherman by trade, and for fun he surfs mountain-sized waves around the world. Being in the sea keeps him connected to his passion, makes him more confident, and lets him live the way he wants.

programme.title: The kayak king
programme.desc: The crew finds an epic sand hill for Poopies to ride the kayak down in Maui. The crew is still on Maui hitting some killer waves on boards and kayaks then they find an epic sand hill for Poopies to ride the kayak down.

programme.title: Last call for Mr Paul
programme.desc: A lot of people run through an airport when they’re late for their flight. Pro freerunner Jason Paul just does it a little differently. A lot of people run through an airport when they’re late for their flight. Pro freerunner Jason Paul just does it a little differently, and along the way he sees parts of the airport most passengers never do.
